race.comment: Open race to close out the card. FIRST EMPIRE (16) got the maiden out of the way in impressive fashion before being tipped out for further time to furnish. Revved up for this with a recent trial and looks the runner in this field with the most upside. Ideally placed to score. The well-related HEESEN (8) (half to 2xG3 winner California Zimbol) just missed the frame in Saturday grade last time out and will find this task a touch easier. Can play a major role in the finish. UNSTOPABULL (3) hails from the champion Waller yard and can run a big race while fresh. ACAPPELLA SUN (6) will be fitter for that first-up hit-out and is capable of sharp improvement. The well-related AMUSEANTES (10) (half to G1 winner Startantes) next in line.
